        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:56PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 456 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mill Creek, or 18 miles southwest of Elkins, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mill Creek, Dailey, and Huttonsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Charleston West Virginia.</instruction>
